				<p><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-374 size-full aligncenter" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08268.jpg" alt="Local in Sapa" width="2894" height="2303" /></p><p>Ha Long Bay is impressive. The boat was beautiful. The food was AMAZING. The activities are alright, but not breathtaking. A couple of hours kayaking and visiting a fisherman village. They also let us swim for 30 minutes in open water, which was nice. We missed being able to swim at some beach but this is forbidden by the government. Obviously, you have no independence as everything is planned.</p><p>On the plus side, the sunset was the most beautiful we&#8217;ve ever seen in our life.</p><p><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-417 size-full aligncenter" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08381.jpg" alt="The views were amazing" width="3600" height="2026" /></p><h4 style="text-align: center;"><b>Experience: Sapa wins by a little</b></h4><p style="text-align: center;"><b> </b></p><h2><strong>Comfort</strong></h2><p>If you&#8217;re going to Sapa you&#8217;re ready to trek mountains, sleep in a maybe not very comfortable homestay, get muddy if it rains, etc. For Ha Long Bay, you literally feel like Paris Hilton and you don&#8217;t need to move a finger. Just relax and enjoy the cruise with your Chihuahua!</p><p><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-415 size-full aligncenter" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08358.jpg" alt="Rafa in the boat" width="3600" height="2026" /></p><h4 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Comfort: very easy win for Ha Long Bay</strong></h4><p style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></p><h2><strong>Just tell me already&#8230;Ha Long Bay or Sapa?</strong></h2><p>If you have the time and the budget, do BOTH. Especially because both experiences are unique and are so different from each other. However, If we had to choose only one, <strong>we would choose Sapa, </strong>just because we had a really authentic experience, one of those that makes travelling so rewarding.</p><p style="text-align: center;"><em>What would you choose? Have you already been to any of the two? We would love to hear about your experience!</em></p><p><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-367 size-full aligncenter" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/sapa6.jpg" alt="Sapa mountains" width="4800" height="2606" /><img decoding="async" class="wp-image-366 size-full aligncenter" src="https://itfeelsgoodtobelost.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/dsc08034-2.jpg" alt="Sapa in a sunny day is just too much" width="4800" height="2701" /></p>					</div>
